1.Get input from user for salary, if the salary is below 10,000 display as unskilled labour and 
if salary is between 11,000 to 15,000 display as skilled labour. 
If salary is above 15,000 display as manager. The user gives input as whole number
import java.util.Scanner;
public class assignment4 {
public static void main(String[] args) {
	Scanner scan=new Scanner(System.in);
	System.out.println("enter the salary");
	int salary=scan.nextInt();
	if(salary<10000){
		System.out.println("unskilled labour");
	}
	else if((salary>=11000)&&(salary<=15000)) {
		System.out.println("skilled labour");
		}
	else if(salary>15000) {
		System.out.println("manager");
	}
	else {
		System.out.println("not a labour");
	}
	scan.close();
		}
}

2. Using the For-Loop print even numbers like 2,4,6,8 till 20.

public class assignment4 {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
	for(int a=1;a<=20;a++) {
       if(a%2==0) { 
       System.out.println("even numbers:"+a);
     }
   }
		 }}
